        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4429563404" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5324168491358901494">I picked this up to test the waters before jumping head first into ‘The Hunchback of Notre Dame’ (chonky ol’ book!) but I genuinely feel, having just finished this short tale, like I have a huge weight on my shoulders. This was an extremely grim and stark perspective of what the death penalty is to those it is handed down to. Victor Hugo delves into the sheer brutality of the reality of what the ‘condemned man’ goes through, and it is well written even if it did take a while to get used to. <br/><br/>I’ve</span>
  <span id="freeText5324168491358901494" style="display:none">I picked this up to test the waters before jumping head first into ‘The Hunchback of Notre Dame’ (chonky ol’ book!) but I genuinely feel, having just finished this short tale, like I have a huge weight on my shoulders. This was an extremely grim and stark perspective of what the death penalty is to those it is handed down to. Victor Hugo delves into the sheer brutality of the reality of what the ‘condemned man’ goes through, and it is well written even if it did take a while to get used to. <br /><br />I’ve closed the pages feeling particularly overwhelmed but glad - if that’s even the right word to describe it - to have read it. Haunting is probably the accurate word to use here. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5324168491358901494" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

